For workouts lasting greater than or equal to 90 minutes, high carbohydrate (2-3g/kg body weight), moderate protein, low-fat meal, 300-500 kcals, ~2hours before activity is consumed. Fat and fiber intake is kept low to prevent stomach discomfort.
Drink 400-600ml (14-22oz) before workout for optimal hydration
Eats simple carbohydrate liquids or gels, food, 30-60 grams every hour (120-240 kcals)
Consumes 150-300ml (6-12oz) ever 15-20 min as water or energy drink
High carbohydrate (1.5g/kg), moderate protein (6g) snack (200calories) within 15-60min of workout (or can be a high carbohydrate, moderate protein meal)
At 2 hours consumes a meal high in carbohydrate, moderate in protein and low in fat
Drinks 450-675ml(16-24oz) for every lb of body weight lost

Registered Dietitian Consult

For workouts lasting greater than or equal to 90 minutes, high carbohydrate (2-3g/kg body weight), moderate protein, low-fat meal, 300-500 kcals, ~2hours before activity is consumed. Fat and fiber intake is kept low to prevent stomach discomfort.
Drink 400-600ml (14-22oz) before workout for optimal hydration
Eats simple carbohydrate liquids or gels, food, 30-60 grams every hour (120-240 kcals)
Consumes 150-300ml (6-12oz) ever 15-20 min as water or energy drink
High carbohydrate (1.5g/kg), moderate protein (6g) snack (200calories) within 15-60min of workout (or can be a high carbohydrate, moderate protein meal)
At 2 hours consumes a meal high in carbohydrate, moderate in protein and low in fat
Drinks 450-675ml(16-24oz) for every lb of body weight lost

Registered Dietitian Consult

For workouts lasting greater than or equal to 90 minutes, high carbohydrate (2-3g/kg body weight), moderate protein, low-fat meal, 300-500 kcals, ~2hours before activity is consumed. Fat and fiber intake is kept low to prevent stomach discomfort.
Drink 400-600ml (14-22oz) before workout for optimal hydration
Eats simple carbohydrate liquids or gels, food, 30-60 grams every hour (120-240 kcals)
Consumes 150-300ml (6-12oz) ever 15-20 min as water or energy drink
High carbohydrate (1.5g/kg), moderate protein (6g) snack (200calories) within 15-60min of workout (or can be a high carbohydrate, moderate protein meal)
At 2 hours consumes a meal high in carbohydrate, moderate in protein and low in fat
Drinks 450-675ml(16-24oz) for every lb of body weight lost

Registered Dietitian Consult

For workouts lasting greater than or equal to 90 minutes, high carbohydrate (2-3g/kg body weight), moderate protein, low-fat meal, 300-500 kcals, ~2hours before activity is consumed. Fat and fiber intake is kept low to prevent stomach discomfort.
Drink 400-600ml (14-22oz) before workout for optimal hydration
Eats simple carbohydrate liquids or gels, food, 30-60 grams every hour (120-240 kcals)
Consumes 150-300ml (6-12oz) ever 15-20 min as water or energy drink
High carbohydrate (1.5g/kg), moderate protein (6g) snack (200calories) within 15-60min of workout (or can be a high carbohydrate, moderate protein meal)
At 2 hours consumes a meal high in carbohydrate, moderate in protein and low in fat
Drinks 450-675ml(16-24oz) for every lb of body weight lost

Registered Dietitian Consult

For workouts lasting greater than or equal to 90 minutes, high carbohydrate (2-3g/kg body weight), moderate protein, low-fat meal, 300-500 kcals, ~2hours before activity is consumed. Fat and fiber intake is kept low to prevent stomach discomfort.
Drink 400-600ml (14-22oz) before workout for optimal hydration
Eats simple carbohydrate liquids or gels, food, 30-60 grams every hour (120-240 kcals)
Consumes 150-300ml (6-12oz) ever 15-20 min as water or energy drink
High carbohydrate (1.5g/kg), moderate protein (6g) snack (200calories) within 15-60min of workout (or can be a high carbohydrate, moderate protein meal)
At 2 hours consumes a meal high in carbohydrate, moderate in protein and low in fat
Drinks 450-675ml(16-24oz) for every lb of body weight lost

Registered Dietitian Consult

For workouts lasting greater than or equal to 90 minutes, high carbohydrate (2-3g/kg body weight), moderate protein, low-fat meal, 300-500 kcals, ~2hours before activity is consumed. Fat and fiber intake is kept low to prevent stomach discomfort.
Drink 400-600ml (14-22oz) before workout for optimal hydration
Eats simple carbohydrate liquids or gels, food, 30-60 grams every hour (120-240 kcals)
Consumes 150-300ml (6-12oz) ever 15-20 min as water or energy drink
High carbohydrate (1.5g/kg), moderate protein (6g) snack (200calories) within 15-60min of workout (or can be a high carbohydrate, moderate protein meal)
At 2 hours consumes a meal high in carbohydrate, moderate in protein and low in fat
Drinks 450-675ml(16-24oz) for every lb of body weight lost
